	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001310_0001"/><!--pb/@n='01'-->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="9" unit="chars"/>Pearl Steamer </p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="12" unit="chars"/><date when="1858-04-21">21<hi rend="sup">st</hi> April 1858</date></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="19" unit="chars"/><add place="inline" rend="gray" hand="#hand01"><choice><abbr>No</abbr><expan>Number</expan></choice> 1</add></p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><persName>Sir George Grey K.C.B.</persName></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="9" unit="chars"/>I have the honour 
<lb/>to forward two <bibl>letters</bibl> for 
<lb/>your Excellency and beg 
<lb/>leave to say that the 
<lb/>Pearl in which we 
<lb/>are sailing for the 
<lb/><placeName><geogName type="river">Zambesi</geogName></placeName> will leave 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001310_0002"/><!--pb/@n='02'-->
<lb/><placeName><geogName type="bay">Table Bay</geogName></placeName> <date when="1858-04-22">tomorrow</date> 
<lb/>forenoon in order to 
<lb/>coal at <placeName><geogName type="bay">Simon's Bay</geogName></placeName>
<lb/>but I shall take the 
<lb/>liberty of calling on 
<lb/>your Excellency before 
<lb/>she departs</p>
<lb/><p rend="center">I am &amp;c </p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>
			
